data.description:
This is a little bit special. To say we're excited is the understatement to beat all understatements. We've gone � tap-takeover-tastic... 

We have Copenhagen's legendary craft brewer #Mikkeller � coming to hang out with us in Cambridge on Sat 9 Sept, so we decided to make the whole long weekend a massive Mikkeller tap-takeover at both #Riverside and #46chestertonroad from 7-10 Sept. 

*Entry is free to both sites.* We'll have 14 taps pouring at #riverside from the 7th, plus the four growler lines at #46chestertonroad, alongside a selection of interesting bottles and cans. We've ordered five pallets of beer from these guys, so come thirsty (to Thirsty). Can't get tickets to Beavertown Extravaganza in London? Come to Cambridge instead... 

But that's not all. We'll have Matthias #Meierer � and his wines alongside - our new producer from Germany's #Mosel Valley. Matthias produces beautiful Riesling wines and has worked with Mikkeller for several years, supplying their Beer Geek Riesling. It was thanks to Matthias that we got the introduction to Mikkeller. He's a rock star, too. The highlight will be a special food and wine pairing evening on Fri 8 Sept at #46chestertonroad, with a flight of Matthias's Rieslings matched to various Asian-influenced goodies from #guerrillakitchen, presented by Matthias himself. 

Tickets for the latter are on Eventbrite at https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/meierer-tasting-with-the-wine-maker-tickets-36922932485. There's no cost to enter the biergarten or Chesterton Road, of course. 

So who's in?!?
data.name: Mikkeller + Meierer Tap-takeover Weekend

data.description:
Easter.... Beer.... Hmmm....Festival time!

Come and join in all thing beerlike at the St.Radegund this April. (Wed 12th -  Sat 15th).  Featuring over 6 real and craft ales from across the country that will be all new to the Rad. Below are a few to give you an idea of what kind of things will be avaiable: 

BACCHUS FRAMBOISE (on keg):
Get fruity in the sunshine with this take on a traditional pint. Bacchus is a delcious belgium lambic beer which is fermented using raspberries. It is one of many modern types of fruit beer that have been inspired by the more traditional kriek beer.

TINY REBEL: (@tinyrebelbrewco)
It all began in 2008  where Brad and Gazz homebrewed on weekends in thier garage in Cardiff, Wales.Officially launched in February 2012, thier award winning core range grew and grew to what it is today. Winner of the 2013 Business Young Achiever award for Wales and the 2014 Welsh Food & Drink award. 

Cwtch -  (rhymes with butch - can mean either cuddle or cubbyhole) 4.6% Deep amber aromatic bitter. Winner of the Champion Beer of Britain 2015 award. 

Fugg Life - British Pale Ale (BPA) An easy drinking 4.2% pale ale, with a rich bitterness before a clean, dry finish. Released June 2016.

THREE BLIND MICE: (@3BlindMiceBrew)
A little closer to home, Three Blind Mice based in Ely can be found around Cambridge and in London. Inventive and innovative with thier beers, they could give any brewery a run for its money. With thier range going from too hoppy to handle to citrusy sweet, there is something for everyone. 

Table Liquor - 2.8% Extremely Llight, hoppy table beer. Easy Drinking. 

Lonely Snake - A well known pick from thier range, 3.6% Light hoppy ale with a varitation in what hops are used, meaning different editions of the same beer. Edition TBD.  

SIGNATURE BREW:  (@SignatureBrew)
"Brewing with music since 2011" being thier tagline, this brewery was born from the brewers love of music but distain over the subpar lager served at gigs. Based in Leyton, East London. 

Red Wedge - Named after the UK political and music movement of the 1980’s, Red Wedge is a 4.7% red ale, using four different hops. A proper taste experience. 

More cask and Keg beer will be available across the festival. We will still have our usual Stowford Press Cider and Lagers on tap. We don't do food unfortunately, but there will be a plethora of snacks (sweet and savoury) to try that are a bit unusual.  

Children welcome until 9pm. FREE ENTRY
WEDS 12TH - FRI 14TH OPEN FROM 3PM  -    SAT NORMAL OPENING HOURS - CLOSED SUNDAY
data.name: Easter BEER Festival 2017

data.description:
IT'S BACK, GREENER (BUT HOPEFULLY NOT RAINIER) THAN EVER BEFORE... 

Thirstyfest is back for its first outing in 2017, marking St Patrick's Day with a bang on Fri 17th March (plus Sat 18th for good measure). We'll be back chez Mackay, taking over the yard/car park behind their store between East Rd and New St, running from 6-11pm each night. And once again, it's *free entry*.

We'll be turning our awesome apres-ski bar green for the occasion, stocking up on some dubious potions from that fair isle across the sea - and encouraging all sorts of leprechaun-like behaviour. Expect a few specials from the food trucks, U2/Sinead O'Connor/Pogues on the PA system, plus the greenest fireworks display you will ever have seen. 

So block out the diaries, spread the word and get practising those jigs...
data.name: Thirstyfest - St Patrick's Day 2017 - Fri 17th

data.description:
Beers at Thirsty with some tapas can be a good way to spend a Tuesday evening, isn’t it?

We are looking forward to welcoming you to Thirsty for a wonderful night of BEER and TAPAS!

On Tuesday, 14 March at 7 PM we’ll take you on a gastronomic tour of the very special place where BEER meets authentic TAPAS.

Thirsty has an amazing selection of beers -no everything is about wine :) – so we will explore some of their selected beers, like IPA, double IPA, Pale Ale, Saison, Fruit infused, Stout, Oatmeal Stout, Larger, Bitter or Barley Wine. I am already working in the menu which will match with 5 of the beers included in the tasting.

But remember, there’s BEER! For a mere £30 per person you’ll be treated to 10 BEERS and 5  TAPAS.

For bookings (required!) call Thirsty at 01223 464436.

Email me at querico@quericotapas.com if you wnat a vegetarian option or have any allergy or dietary requirement.

Look forward to seeing you!
